cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.NE, cs.IT. 

The paper proposes a deep learning network for signal classification using Dual-Tree complex wavelets. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.IT (Information Theory). However, since the focus is on deep learning and classification, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. The use of wavelets for signal processing also suggests cs.CV and cs.IT as possible sub-categories. The application of the proposed network to different datasets suggests cs.SI as another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of computational efficiency as a metric suggests cs.NE as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
